In Pfullendorf, the electricity more expensive
The citizens Pfullendorfs must adapt to higher energy costs.
As the director of the company, Jörg Arne Bias, confirmed to the South courier, on a vierköpfige Pfullendorfer family cost EUR 70 to 90 per year.
The main reason for the increase is the rise of the so-called EEG levy of 5.277 to 6.3 cents per kilowatt-hour.
This levy is newly established in October each year of the four operators of the big electricity lines.
These quantify the costs arising from the energy turning them, they can raise by a levy on the price of electricity.
The Stadtwerke Pfullendorf form the last link in this chain.
The board of the energy company was in its forecasts even as Jörg Arne Bias based on a higher levy.
Now, the specific pay should be calculated before the public could inform their customers about the exact price increase next week.
"We go from an increase of 1 cent plus x," Bias, with the number would be in the vicinity of 2 cents.
